11172590429{margin-top: 5px !important;margin-bottom: 5px !important;}\" el_class=\"heading1\"][vc_column_text]Individuals &amp; businesses which are being pursued for debts.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" el_class=\"services_page_block1\" css=\".vc_custom_1511245248687{padding-top: 60px !important;padding-bottom: 40px !important;}\"][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Services\" font_container=\"tag:h2|font_size:50px|text_align:left|color:{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63}2357565b|line_height:50px\" el_class=\"heading1\" css=\".vc_custom_1511245206774{margin-top: 5px !important;margin-bottom: 20px !important;}\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"services_content\" width=\"2/3\" css=\".vc_custom_1511245389656{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"73 PROPOSAL - ANNULMENT OF BANKRUPTCY\" font_container=\"tag:h5|font_size:20px|text_align:left|color:{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63}23ff8c05|line_height:25px\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Montserrat{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63}3Aregular{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63}2C700|font_style:400{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63}20regular{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63}3A400{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63}3Anormal\" css=\".vc_custom_1511244623087{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 20px !important;}\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"services_text1\"]Fortunately there are provisions within the Bankruptcy Act that enable a bankrupt to have their bankruptcy annulled through a Section 73 proposal. Rather than following the natural course of bankruptcy over 3 years or more, a Section 73 proposal is an approach where if the majority of creditors (in number) &amp; 75{788dc26ed341a45036d0967177cd9b68a8da113477939846be2287efb6288a63} (in dollar value) of those creditors vote to support a resolution, a bankruptcy can be annulled.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"267\" img_size=\"305x305\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_column_text el_class=\".services_text1\"]All Debt Solutions utilise mechanisms within the Bankruptcy Act that allow for the annulment of bankruptcy through the provisions of Section 73, which has the same effect as if the bankruptcy had never occurred.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\".services_text2\"]This gives the former bankrupt a \'fresh start\', and free from all debts covered under the bankruptcy act that occurred before their bankruptcy.[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title=\"Download Pdf\" color=\"warning\" i_align=\"right\" i_icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-long-arrow-right\" add_icon=\"true\" custom_onclick=\"true\" el_id=\"Services_dpbtn\" el_class=\"Services_dpbtn\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\" el_class=\"Services_sidebar\"][vc_widget_sidebar sidebar_id=\"sidebar-9\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]", "Asset protection", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "36-revision-v1", "", "", "2017-11-21 06:57:35", "2017-11-21 06:57:35", "", "36", "http://localhost/Allure/36-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
